					<article>
						<h4>Instructions</h4>
						<!-- single instruction -->
						<div class="single-instruction">
							<header>
								<p>step 1</p>
							</header>
							<p>
								Separate chicken into 8 pieces. Cut drumsticks, thighs, and wings in
								half; cut breasts crosswise into thirds—you will have 18 pieces of
								chicken.
							</p>
						</div>
						<!-- end of single instruction -->
						<!-- single instruction -->
						<div class="single-instruction">
							<header><p>step 2</p></header>
							<p>Heat oil in a 12″ nonstick skillet over medium-high.</p>
						</div>
						<div class="single-instruction">
							<header><p>step 3</p></header>
							<p>
								Cook coriander, cumin, and fennel seeds, dal, curry and bay leaves,
								cloves, and cinnamon until dal are golden, 2–3 minutes.
							</p>
						</div>
						<div class="single-instruction">
							<header><p>step 4</p></header>
							<p>
								Stir in cardamom, turmeric, garlic, onion, and ginger; cook until
								slightly caramelized, 6–8 minutes.
							</p>
						</div>
						<div class="single-instruction">
							<header><p>step 5</p></header>
							<p>Add tomatoes; cook until broken down, 4–5 minutes.</p>
						</div>
						<div class="single-instruction">
							<header><p>step 6</p></header>
							<p>Add chicken and 1⁄2 cup water; boil.</p>
						</div>
						<div class="single-instruction">
							<header><p>step 7</p></header>
							<p>
								Reduce heat to medium-low; cook, covered, until chicken is cooked
								through, about 25 minutes.
							</p>
						</div>
						<div class="single-instruction">
							<header><p>step 8</p></header>
							<p>
								Uncover and increase heat to medium-high. Stir in pepper; simmer
								until slightly thickened, 3–4 minutes.
							</p>
						</div>
						<div class="single-instruction">
							<header><p>step 9</p></header>
							<p>Garnish with cilantro; serve with rice if you like.</p>
						</div>
						<!-- end of single instruction -->
						<!-- single instruction -->
						<!-- end of single instruction -->
					</article>
					<article class="second-column">
						<div>
							<h4>Ingredients</h4>
							<ul class="recipe-content-list">
								<li>
									<p class="single-ingredient">
										2-lb. boneless, skinless chicken thighs
									</p>
								</li>
								<li><p class="single-ingredient">1⁄4 cup canola oil</p></li>
								<li><p class="single-ingredient">3 tbsp. coriander seeds</p></li>
								<li><p class="single-ingredient">1 1⁄2 tbsp. cumin seeds</p></li>
								<li><p class="single-ingredient">1 1⁄2 tsp. fennel seeds</p></li>
								<li>
									<p class="single-ingredient">
										1 1⁄2 tsp. urad dal (skinned split black lentils), rinsed,
										soaked 30 minutes, and drained
									</p>
								</li>
								<li>
									<p class="single-ingredient">10 fresh or frozen curry leaves</p>
								</li>
								<li>
									<p class="single-ingredient">3 Indian or regular bay leaves</p>
								</li>
								<li><p class="single-ingredient">3 whole cloves</p></li>
								<li><p class="single-ingredient">1 stick cinnamon, halved</p></li>
								<li><p class="single-ingredient">1 tsp. ground cardamom</p></li>
								<li><p class="single-ingredient">1⁄2 tsp. ground turmeric</p></li>
								<li>
									<p class="single-ingredient">
										5 cloves garlic, mashed into a paste
									</p>
								</li>
								<li>
									<p class="single-ingredient">1 large yellow onion, minced</p>
								</li>
								<li>
									<p class="single-ingredient">
										1 (2″) piece ginger, peeled and mashed into a paste
									</p>
								</li>
								<li><p class="single-ingredient">Kosher salt, to taste</p></li>
								<li><p class="single-ingredient">2 plum tomatoes, minced</p></li>
								<li>
									<p class="single-ingredient">
										1 1⁄2 tbsp. coarsely ground black pepper
									</p>
								</li>
								<li><p class="single-ingredient">1⁄4 cup chopped cilantro</p></li>
								<li>
									<p class="single-ingredient">
										Cooked white rice, for serving (optional)
									</p>
								</li>
							</ul>
						</div>
